            <h2 class="featurette-heading">About Ivy-Leafed Sida. <span class="text-muted">It'll blow your mind.</span></h2>
            <p class="lead">
                Ivy-leaf sida is native to western North America and has not established in any other country other than Australia. Ivy-leaf sida is not readily grazed by animals and can compete strongly with pastures, particularly in alkaline soils. The known distribution of ivy-leaf sida in Victoria is in the Pyramid Hill - Cohuna area. It is associated with irrigation channels and irrigated pastures.
            
            </p>
        </div>
